    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah that's exactly what's worrying me. it feels like these claims can just come out of nowhere and then i'm stuck dealing with all these hidden threats or unexpected legal monsters. how do people usually protect themselves from these kinds of sudden, unpredictable liabilities in these contracts?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A common way people try to manage these sudden liabilities is by negotiating the scope of the indemnification. You want to make sure you aren't agreeing to cover *everything*, just the things you are directly responsible for. You can try to limit it to claims arising specifically from your negligence or breach of contract, rather than every single possible scenario. It's all about carving out the specific areas where your responsibility ends.",
      "source": "target",
